learningObjectives:
For researchers wanting to adhere to FAIR practies.  Course provides code for exercises.
Introduce what FAIR means especially in relationship to code written for research purposes.
Course is comprehensive covering the research code lifecylce, describing good practices at each stage:
 Creating a github project (along with practices to help with version control); 
Practices to help with reproductibility (eg creating reproducible environment for other reseaerches, dependencies trees, VMs); 
Practices to annotate code to ensure that others can understand and use the code;
Code structure recommendations; Testing and Documentation practices
